## <span id="Introductie"></span>Introduction

The IBIS connector framework enables import and export of data from and
to external systems. The connector uses vendor-specific modules for
communication with external systems. A number of modules are available
out-of-the-box. In case an external system cannot be connected using an
existing module, a custom module can be developed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)


## <span id="Staging area"></span>Staging area

Each connector contains a staging area for intermediate storage of
objects.

For more information how to use the staging area, see also the
[Staging Area](./IBIS_StagingArea) documentation

## <span id="Join / Project / Disconnect"></span>Join / Project / Disconnect

Join, project and disconnect are the operations that handle the
connection between a staging area object and an IBIS entity. The diagram
below describes the flow each staging area object follows during a
synchronize action.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Join

Link a staging area object to an existing IBIS entity using predefined
match rules.  
Match rules are defined on the Matching rules tab of the connector using
the Dynamic LINQ language.

-   Multiple match rules can be specified
-   Match rules are applied in the order displayed
-   Once a match is found, subsequent match rules will be skipped
-   The name of the successful match scenario is stored on the staging
    entity
-   You can drag and drop the match rules to change the order in which
    they are processed.
-   Property names are CASE SENSITIVE

![](data:image/png;base64,)

NOTE: Match rules result in one or more database queries for each object
that is being processed. To speed up the process, add database indexes
to the table in question for the fields on which you are matching.

### Examples


| _01_52_Dienstverband_SSOAccountNaam == "{accountName}" |      Match an IBIS entity by comparing _01_52_Dienstverband_SSOAccountNaam to the string value stored in the accountName property of the staging area object     |
|------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| ID == Guid.Parse("{PersonId}")                         | Match an IBIS entity by comparing ID to the result value of Guid.Parse, which uses the value stored in the PersonId property of the staging area object as input |

## <span id="Project"></span>Project

Create a new IBIS entity for an existing staging area object in case no
match can be found using the Join process. This feature is disabled by
default, and can be enabled by setting the value of the Provisioning
option to Create new objects in IBIS on the General tab of the connector

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## <span id="Disconnect"></span>Disconnect

Disconnect a staging area object from an IBIS entity when one or more of
the following apply:

-   the external system no longer supplies the object during a Full
    Import operation
-   the IBIS object is removed
-   the IBIS object matches the deprovision filter set on the connector

**Disconnect because the object is removed from the external system**  
On disconnect, the action specified in Disconnect action will be
performed on the IBIS object

-   Ignore - Do nothing
-   Remove - Remove the associated IBIS entity
-   Expire - Expire the associated IBIS entity

Once the specified disconnect action is successfully executed, the
object will be removed from the staging area.  
**Disconnect because the object is removed from the IBIS or matches the
deprovision filter**  
On disconnect, the object will be removed from the external system,
except when a special action is set in the module configuration. Once
the action is complete, the object will be removed from the staging
area.

## <span id="Attribute mappings"></span>Attribute mappings

Attribute mappings are used to set the value of properties (attributes)
on connected objects in IBIS and/or the connected system. Attribute
mappings are processed during the Sync operation.  
Configuration of attribute mappings is done on the Attribute mappings
tab of the connector. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

NOTE: When importing values to a decimal column (for instance, working
hours per week), the regional settings of the application pool user are
used for value determination. In case an incorrect value is imported,
check the regional settings, and make sure Load user profile is
enabled on the application pool

There are two types of attribute mappings:

-   Import : Update a property on an IBIS entity
-   Export : Update a property on an object in the connected system

An attribute mapping consists of the following properties:

|           Part           |                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
|:------------------------:|:---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------:|
| Property                 | The name of the property to set                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| Value expression         | An expression which can be parsed by the dynamic lookup module. The dynamic lookup module will return the final value. <br>More information on the dynamic lookup module can be found in the workflow documentation. Check the next section for some examples.    <br>If you want to reference a value from the staging entity, start the value expression with the % character. This way, the expression will be resolved against the staging entity. |
| Only on import provision | Set the value only during an import provision action (meaning, when a IBIS object is created for an already existing external object). <br>Once this value is staged, it will remain staged until successfully written to IBIS (import) or the connected system (export). <br>Any other property mappings to the target property will not be applied as long as there is a pending import/export value with this flag.                                |
| Only on export provision | Set the value only during an export provision action (meaning, when a external object is created for an already existing IBIS object).<br> Once this value is staged, it will remain staged until successfully written to IBIS (import) or the connected system (export). <br>Any other property mappings to the target property will not be applied as long as there is a pending import/export value with this flag.                                |
| Only on join             | Set the value only during a join action (an existing IBIS object gets connected to an existing external object). <br>Once this value is staged, it will remain staged until successfully written to IBIS (import) or the connected system (export). <br>Any other property mappings to the target property will not be applied as long as there is a pending import/export value with this flag.                                                      |
| Only when empty          | Set the value only if the target property value is null or empty                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| Only on object mutation  | Only set the value when one or more (non mutation only properties) are staged for import/export (depending on the flow direction)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |
| Realtime                 | By default, the connector only synchronizes and exports data when either manually triggered or called from a runprofile. <br>Enable this option to trigger realtime synchronization and export of a single object when the value of this attribute is changed in IBIS. <br>On synchronization/export, the complete object is evaluated and exported, thus not only this attribute                                                                     |

## Examples

| Direction |       Target property       |                  Value expression                 |                                                                                              Description                                                                                             |
|:---------:|:---------------------------:|:-------------------------------------------------:|:----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------:|
| Import    | _09_39_Alias_Displayname    | {?{DisplayName},trim()}                           | Set the value of IBIS property _09_39_Alias_Displayname to the value of the DisplayName property in the external system, where any whitespaces on the beginning and end of the value will be removed |
| Import    | _09_36_Alias_Aanmeldsysteem | DOMAINNAME                                        | Set the value of IBIS property _09_36_Alias_Aanmeldsysteem to the fixed value 'DOMAINNAME'                                                                                                           |
| Import    | _09_38_Alias_UPN            | {userPrincipalName}                               | Set the value of IBIS property _09_38_Alias_UPN to the exact value of the userPrincipalName property in the external system                                                                          |
| Export    | phone                       | {_01_61_Dienstverband_Telefoonnummer}             | Set the value of the phone property in the external system to the exact value of the _01_61_Dienstverband_Telefoonnummer property of the IBIS entity                                                 |
| Export    | description                 | {?workflow(3cad75bb-9533-4cd2-8d48-a3aff3f6f6b0)} | Set the value of the description property in the external system to the ReturnValue argument of the workflow with ID 3cad75bb-9533-4cd2-8d48-a3aff3f6f6b0                                            |


## <span id="Import / Export actions"></span>Import / Export actions

The connector is able to run a PowerShell script at the following
moments:

-   Pre import, before the import from the connected system starts
-   Post import, after successful import from the connected system
-   Pre export, before the export to the connected system starts
-   Post export, after successful export to the connected system

The PowerShell script will be executed on the machine or app-service
where IBIS is installed or, when using an agent, the machine on which
the agent is hosted. Connecting to another computer can be done from
within the script.

It's mandatory to provide a username and password, except when running
in Azure.

On-premises IBIS will not allow to run the scripts under the application
pool user.

## <span id="Filters"></span>Filters

Filters (criteria) can be configured on a connector in order to:

-   Exclude objects from being created/updated in IBIS
-   Include objects that should be created in the connected system
-   Disconnect objects from IBIS
-   Disconnect objects from the connected system

The filters can be configured on the ***Filters*** tab of the connector
settings. Filters are written in the dynamic LINQ expression markup.

<u>In order to use a dynamic property in a filter, specify it as:
DynamicProperties\["propertyname"\]</u>

|                                        Filter                                       |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            |
|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Do not create an IBIS object for external objects that match the following criteria | This filter is applied against the hologram of disconnected staging area entities. Entities that match the filter will be excluded from further processing. The exclusion reason is visible on the Exclusion tab of the staging entity.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            |
| Disconnect IBIS object when external object matches the following criteria          | This filter is applied against the hologram of connected staging area entities. Entities that match the filter will be disconnected from their IBIS object.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |
| Create external objects for IBIS objects that match the following criteria          | This filter is applied to IBIS objects. Entities that match the filter will be created in the external system. If this filter is not set, external objects will never be created.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| Disconnect external object when IBIS object matches the following criteria          | This filter is applied to IBIS objects. Connected entities that match the filter will be deprovisioned from the external system.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |

*The filter screen on the connector settings page*  
![](data:image/png;base64,)

## <span id="Thresholds"></span>Thresholds

Thresholds can be used to abort processing when certain limits are
reached. Thresholds can be set for Import (sync) and Export operations.

To configure thresholds, open the Thresholds tab of the connector: 
<br>
![](data:image/png;base64,)

|                 Setting                |                                                               Description                                                              |
|:--------------------------------------:|:--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------:|
| Use object count instead of percentage | Enabled: the number specified will be used as object count threshold<br> <br>Disabled: the number specified will be used as percentage |
| Create                                 | The total percentage (or count) of objects that will be created                                                                        |
| Update                                 | The total percentage (or count) of objects that will be updated                                                                        |
| Delete                                 | The total percentage (or count) of objects that will be deleted                                                                        |

When a threshold violation occurs, processing is aborted immediately
and:

-   A log entry is written to the system log

<!-- -->

-   A custom workflow event is triggered

<!-- -->

-   ImportThresholdViolation
-   ExportThresholdViolation

## <span id="IDM Number"></span>IDM Number

If the connector targets an IDM number object (like iDossier or
aliasDossier) it's possible to perform a lookup for an IDM number during
the sync operation. In case an IDM number is found, it will be added to
the pending import property collection and stored in database during
commit.

If no lookup scenarios are configured, IBIS will use the default IDM
number logic (configured in IBIS General Settings) to perform a lookup
or generate a new IDM number.

Lookup scenarios can be defined on the **IDM Number generation** tab of
the connector.

In case you do not see this tab the target object is not an IDM Number
object.

The IDM number lookup scenarios will be applied during the sync
operation in the order they appear on the settings tab. To change the
order, drag the scenario to a different position.

Scenarios are only applied when a staging area object:

-   Does not contain an IBIS object ID
-   Is not connected through a join rule

Rules exist of 3 properties, which are described in the following table;

|     Property     |                                                                                   Description                                                                                   |
|:----------------:|:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------:|
| Name             | The name of the scenario. In case the scenario results in a match, this name will be stored on the staging area object for future reference (in the property IdmNumberRuleName) |
| Ibis object type | The object type to search for an existing IDM number                                                                                                                            |
| Match expression | A Linq expression to filter the collection of IBIS objects of the type specified by Ibis object type                                                                            |
| Delete           | The total percentage (or count) of objects that will be deleted                                                                                                                 |

In case a rule results in multiple matches, the first result in the
collection will be used.

## <span id="Agent"></span>Agent

IBIS includes a connector agent which makes it possible to communicate
with systems that are otherwise unreachable by IBIS. The agent runs on a
Windows machine as a background service or standalone executable.



Once started the agent opens a secure tunnel to IBIS using the HTTPS
protocol. Since the tunnel is agent-initiated, no firewall rules are
needed other than the agent being able to access IBIS through HTTPS.

![](data:image/png;base64,%)

Connector commands are initiated by IBIS and executed on the agent. The
result data is sent back to IBIS. For example, when importing data from
an Active Directory:

1.  IBIS sends the **Import** command to the on-premises agent along
    with the module parameters
2.  The agent fetches the data from Active Directory using the specified
    module parameters
3.  The result data is sent back to IBIS
4.  IBIS processes the result data

At startup, the agent registers itself with IBIS. Additionally, the
agent sends a status report which is stored in the IBIS database on the
connector entity. The report can be displayed on the connector settings
screen (on the Agent tab).

*<u>The report is only visible after the agent successfully connected at
least one time</u>*

![](data:image/png;base64,)

When the agent is shut-down (or communications is lost for a period of
time) IBIS unregisters the agent and an error will be shown on the
connector index page

<img
src="data:image/png;base64,"
class="img-fluid my-5 w-75 mx-auto d-block border" />

## Configuring a connector to use an agent

1.  Open the connector in IBIS and navigate to the **Agent** tab

![](data:image/png;base64,)

2.  Enable the ***This connector uses an agent*** checkbox and save the
    connector settings

<!-- -->

3.  Install, configure and start the agent by following the steps in the
    next sections

<!-- -->

4.  To disable the use of an agent once enabled, uncheck the ***This
    connector uses an agent*** *checkbox and save the connector
    settings*

## <span id="_Toc67299397"></span>Installing the agent

1.  On the connector Agent tab, click the ***download*** button to
    download the latest version of the agent as a compressed ZIP file

<!-- -->

2.  Copy the ZIP file to the machine that should host the agent

<!-- -->

3.  Create a folder for the agent and extract the agent zip file to that
    folder.



4.  In case the agent will run as a specific user, grant that user
    account read/write access to the agent folder



5.  Start a PowerShell session with elevated privileges and change the
    directory to the agent installation folder



6.  Run the following command to unblock the downloaded files:
    **Unblock-File -Path \***



7.  Run **.\\*ps1*** and follow the on-screen instructions to configure
    the agent.  
    The table below describes the various options that are presented
    during configuration



8.  After configuration, grant CRUD permissions on the agent
    installation folder to the agent service account and local
    administrators, <u>remove all other permissions</u>

The name must not contain spaces, and only characters in the range [0-9] [a-Z] [-_.]<br> <br> <br> <br>For example: IbisAgent_SqlConnector1                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |
| IBIS URL                                      | The URL of the IBIS installation the agent will connect to.
